text.tspan: Annual greenhouse gas emissions by world region, 1850 to
Greenhouse gas emissions include carbon dioxide, methane and nitrous oxide from all sources, including agriculture and land use
change. They are measured in carbon dioxide-equivalents over a 100-year timescale.
Data source: Our World in Data based on Jones et al. (2023); Jones et al. (2023)
